  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2 - Achieving Socially Responsible Land Based Investments in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The current proposal seeks to dedicate attention to unpacking the impacts of large scale land acquisition to highlight impacts on the most vulnerable groups, create awareness on these impacts and work together with all stakeholders to define and integrate mitigating measures into the current work of developing national guidelines.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposal seeks to further accelerate discussions on rights abuses in large scale land acquisition and use by generating evidence with which key stakeholders are engaged; and a review of national guidelines for large scale land-acquisition thereon will incorporate GESI considerations to meet the aspirations 
The key strategies proposed are:
a- Evidence based research on the disaggregated impacts of land scale land acquisition Public Education, 
b- Sensitization and Awareness Creation campaigns on the different impacts of large scale land acquisition
c- Advocacy and dialogue with policy actors and implementers for the incorporation of GESI considerations in national guidelines for responsible land based investments
d- Capacity strengthening for mainstreaming GESI in the implementation of guidelines for responsible land based investments.</narrative>
  </description>
